
Here are the fixes I made to the Sunshine '69 HTML files:

1. Fixed broken internal links:
- Updated href attributes to point to the correct .html files
- Example: <a href="revealed.htm"> changed to <a href="revealed.html">

2. Background image CSS fixes:  
- Added background-repeat: no-repeat to body tag CSS to prevent tiling
- Example: 
  <body background="images/sunshine69.gif">
  changed to
  <body style="background: url('images/sunshine69.gif') no-repeat;">

3. Validated and updated deprecated HTML:
- Replaced <center> tags with <div style="text-align:center;">  
- Added alt attributes to <img> tags
- Removed obsolete attributes like bgcolor, border, etc.

4. Checked for missing assets:
- Verified all referenced images exist in the images/ directory
- Verified all referenced .ram audio files exist in ram/ directory
- Missing files documented in missing_assets.txt

5. Miscellaneous fixes:
- Fixed broken HTML entities (&name with no semicolon) 
- Consistent casing on .html and .gif extensions
- Removed stray / and > characters outside tags

Remaining to-dos:
1. Consider converting .ram audio to mp3 for compatibility 
2. Locate or replace missing assets listed in missing_assets.txt
3. Optimize image file sizes for faster loading

Change log and missing asset manifest attached. All HTML has been validated and tested. Zip file contains updated site files.

